[Your Website Name] ("we," "our," "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information when you use our tool to display followers or likes retrieved from the Facebook/Instagram API.

Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. By using our tool, you agree to the terms described here. If you do not agree, please discontinue use of the tool.

1. Information We Collect
When you use our tool, we may collect the following information through the Facebook/Instagram API:

User IDs or profile names associated with your account.
Number of followers or likes on your account or posts.
Publicly available account metrics or insights as permitted by the API.
We do not collect or store your sensitive personal information, such as passwords or payment details.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information to:

Display your followers or likes as per your request.
Provide insights and analytics based on the data retrieved.
Improve and optimize our tool’s performance and user experience.
3. Data Storage and Security
Temporary Data Use: We only use the data retrieved from the Facebook/Instagram API for display purposes. This data is not stored on our servers unless explicitly required for certain features (e.g., historical insights).
Encryption: All API communications are secured with industry-standard encryption to protect your data during transmission.
Minimal Storage: If any data is temporarily stored, we ensure its deletion after fulfilling the intended purpose.
4. Sharing Your Information
We do not sell, rent, or share your data with third parties, except:

To comply with legal obligations or enforce our policies.
With your explicit consent or at your request.
5. Third-Party Services
Our tool uses the Facebook/Instagram API, and your data is subject to their respective privacy policies.

Facebook Privacy Policy: https://www.facebook.com/policy.php
Instagram Privacy Policy: https://privacycenter.instagram.com/policy
We encourage you to review these policies to understand how these platforms handle your data.

6. Your Rights
Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your data:

Access: Request details about the data we process.
Correction: Update any incorrect or incomplete information.
Deletion: Request deletion of any data we store about you.
Revocation of Consent: Disconnect our tool’s access to your Facebook/Instagram account at any time.
To exercise these rights, contact us at [Your Email Address].

7. Cookies and Tracking
We do not use cookies or tracking technologies to gather personal data related to this tool.

8. Children’s Privacy
Our tool is not intended for individuals under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect data from them.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices or for legal and operational reasons. The updated version will be available on this page with the effective date.

